race.comment: SHE'S A TANGO (6) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, paving the way for a half a length win at this track over 340m in 19.79. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Ideally placed to take this out. TRAIN TICKET (1) proved too good on debut over 340m at this track to score by 2 lengths (19.94). Can use the low draw to advantage. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. BRONTE BEACH (2) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (20.85) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. SLICK OLIVE (7) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.
